      <para id="import-auto-id1327216">The wind&#8217;s speed and direction are consistent with the significant effect the wind has on the total velocity of the plane, as seen in <link target-id="import-auto-id1546060"/>. Because the plane is fighting a strong combination of crosswind and head-wind, it ends up with a total velocity significantly less than its velocity relative to the air mass as well as heading in a different direction.</para>
